### H2: Step 2 — Understand What Landlords Look For

#### H3: Credit Score Requirements for Renting an Apartment
**Instruction:** Provide the explicit credit score ranges landlords use (Poor: 300–579, Fair: 580–669, Good: 670–739, Very Good: 740–799, Excellent: 800–850), note that most mid-market landlords want 620+, and explain that luxury buildings often require 700+. Reference where to check your score for free (AnnualCreditReport.com).

#### H3: Proof of Income and the 3x Rent Rule
**Instruction:** Explain that most landlords require gross income of 2.5–3x monthly rent. List accepted income documents: pay stubs (2–3 most recent), W-2s/tax returns (2 years), bank statements (2–3 months), employment offer letter, and 1099s/business contracts for self-employed applicants.

#### H3: Rental History and References
**Instruction:** Explain what landlords check in rental history (prior evictions, payment records) and what references to prepare (prior landlords, employers, professional contacts). Flag that a first-time renter with no rental history should proactively gather employment references.

